      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern historians view the UN's effectiveness as a deeply mixed bag, often highlighting its structural failures. While it has managed to prevent some localized conflicts from escalating, its inability to stop major aggressions, such as those in Ukraine or Gaza, proves its inherent weakness. The organization is consistently hampered by the veto power of its most powerful members, which paralyzes meaningful action when great power interests clash. Therefore, its record is one of limited, often reactive, success rather than proactive global peace enforcement.",
