      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that a flawed institution is better than chaos is a comforting narrative, but it ignores the moral and legal failures of the current system. While the UN prevents *some* outright global war, it has demonstrably failed to prevent humanitarian catastrophes and systemic oppression, which is a profound failure of its mandate. A truly effective international order would require accountability, not just the management of inevitable conflict among the powerful.",
      "source": "target",
